## Syntax Example

```dart
String? databaseName = null;

// If databaseName is NULL... use 'Guest' instead!
String displayName = databaseName ?? 'Guest';

print(displayName); // Prints 'Guest'
```
The `??` operator asks: *"Is the left side empty? If yes, use the right side instead."*

## Null-Aware Method Calling

What if you want to call a method like `.length` on a nullable string, but DO NOT want to crash if it's empty?
Use the **Null-Aware Access Operator (`?.`)**!

```dart
String? message = null;

// If message is null, it aborts the .length call and safely returns null!
print(message?.length); 
```
It acts like a protective shield before allowing the dot operator to execute.

